{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1492856203,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5NjM2MzMzMA==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/110#issuecomment-296363330"},"message":"There's probably going to be more bring-up issues than these as I don't have anything with PowerVR to try. but let's give it a go. Is there any QEmu- workable devimage to start with?\n\nProbing for CLOCK_MONOTONIC v. CLOCK_MONOTONIC_RAW should be added to the build system anyhow so I'll look into that. Advanced engine features will probably sting for a bit, so lets start easier. Add -DNO_FSRV=ON to your cmake and it should ignore the frameservers entirely for the time being. How far do you get then?\n\nI've built on ARM in other environments (non-public android port and raspberry- pi) so there's something else going on with the TIOCSIG..","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"5882dffa8f545c1c47d03005e5d37eead4bd62d8"},"timestamp":1492947116,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5NjQzNjg5Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/110#issuecomment-296436896"},"message":"Hi :)\n\nSome good news first: \n\n- Compilation completes successfully when frameservers are turned off.\n- It also completes successfully when they are turned on though, provided the following lines are added to /src/frameserver/terminal/default/tsm/shl-pty.c :\n\n#ifndef TIOCSIG\n#define FIOQSIZE 0x545E\n#include \u003casm/ioctls.h\u003e\n#define TIOCSIG  _IOW('T', 0x36, int)  /* pty: generate signal */\n#endif\n\nThe Open Pandora runs Linux 3.2.84, and TIOCSIG doesn't seem to be present in our include files. So I just copied the relevant bit from a more recent kernel version:\n\nhttps://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux-stable.git/tree/arch/arm/include/asm/ioctls.h?id=refs/tags/v3.2.88\n\nhttps://git.kernel.org/pub/scm/linux/kernel/git/stable/linux-stable.git/tree/include/asm-generic/ioctls.h?id=refs/tags/v3.2.88\n\nCheers, Sam","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"5882dffa8f545c1c47d03005e5d37eead4bd62d8"},"timestamp":1492948308,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5NjQzNzg5Mw==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/110#issuecomment-296437893"},"message":"And now the bad news :\n\n./arcan -p ../data/resources/ ../data/appl/welcome, when Aran is built with \"-DVIDEO_PLATFORM=sdl\" and \"-DAGP_PLATFORM=gl21\", crashes with the following error message:\n\nagp lookup(glEnableVertexAttribArray) failed, missing req. symbol.\nAborted\n\nN.B: the Open Pandora is not compatible with stock OpenGL, only with OpenGL ES... In order to run OpenGL applications, we use a wrapper library, gl4es:\n\nhttps://github.com/ptitseb/gl4es\n\nLooks like glEnableVertexAttribArray is not yet implemented in this library. I'll ask the author if he could do something about it.\n\nNext, I tried to compile Arcan with  \"-DAGP_PLATFORM=gles2\". But this time, it failed with the following error message:\n\n[ 41%] Building C object CMakeFiles/arcan.dir/platform/agp/glshared.c.o\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c: In function ���agp_rendertarget_swap���:\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c:60:21: error: ���GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING��� undeclared (first use in this function)\n  env-\u003eget_integer_v(GL_DRAW_FRAMEBUFFER_BINDING, \u0026cfbo);\n                     ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c:60:21: note: each undeclared identifier is reported only once for each function it appears in\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c: In function ���agp_pipeline_hint���:\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c:384:40: error: ���GL_FILL��� undeclared (first use in this function)\n   env-\u003epolygon_mode(GL_FRONT_AND_BACK, GL_FILL);\n                                        ^~~~~~~\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c: In function ���agp_update_vstore���:\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c:538:21: error: ���GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH��� undeclared (first use in this function)\n   env-\u003epixel_storei(GL_UNPACK_ROW_LENGTH, 0);\n                     ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c: In function ���agp_submit_mesh���:\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c:776:42: error: ���GL_LINE��� undeclared (first use in this function)\n     env-\u003epolygon_mode(GL_FRONT_AND_BACK, GL_LINE);\n                                          ^~~~~~~\n/media/Pandora1/dev/arcan/arcan/src/platform/agp/glshared.c:782:42: error: ���GL_FILL��� undeclared (first use in this function)\n     env-\u003epolygon_mode(GL_FRONT_AND_BACK, GL_FILL);\n                                          ^~~~~~~\nCMakeFiles/arcan.dir/build.make:878: recipe for target 'CMakeFiles/arcan.dir/platform/agp/glshared.c.o' failed\nmake[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/arcan.dir/platform/agp/glshared.c.o] Error 1\nCMakeFiles/Makefile2:68: recipe for target 'CMakeFiles/arcan.dir/all' failed\nmake[1]: *** [CMakeFiles/arcan.dir/all] Error 2\nMakefile:127: recipe for target 'all' failed\nmake: *** [all] Error 2\n\nWhat am I doing wrong ?\n\nCheers, Sam","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"},"timestamp":1492955519,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDI5NjQ0NDc3MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/letoram/arcan/issues/110#issuecomment-296444771"},"message":"You might have some luck jumping back a version or two, a lot of work in the master branch on getting multi-vendor-multi-GPU + driver hotswapping working and GLES2/3 is getting much less attention than GL21 - hoping that over time, GL21, Vulkan and Software will be the only drawing APIs  that are needed.\n\nHow's the 0.5.1 or 0.5.0 tag reacting?","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"e6c152d440109efdc7afc4e9ac4ac193043f8f68"}